CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 16, 1969, pg. 19, reads: "TEEING OFF - If one didn't care to swim, there were other events planned to suit the individual mood. This quartet, also from this year's Best Dressed found active sports to their liking.  Shown 'teeing off' on the putting field at Washington Plaza are from left: Miss Lynette May, Mrs. Gerri Walker, one of the hostesses for the party; Miss Shirley Jenkins and Miss Alberta Thompson, also a party hostess. - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Four women, including left to right: Lynette May, Gerri Walker, Shirley Jenkins, and Alberta Thompson hitting golf balls at Washington Plaza putting field, with Civic Arena in background, another version
